> New to pulled mushrooms? Allow us to introduce you! Thanks to their savory, 
> umami flavor and hearty, meaty texture, pulled mushrooms are an ideal meat 
> substitute in all kinds of dishes. Here, they're paired with roasted broccoli, 
> pickled veggies, and Korean-style bulgogi sauce to make satisfying rice bowls. 
> Finish 'em with a drizzle of spicy mayo and crackly sesame seeds!

== Rice ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry 
@broccoli{8%ounce}, @radishes{3%unit}, @onion{1%unit}, @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}, 
@bulgogi sauce{4%ounce}, @spicy mayo{4%tablespoon}, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, 
@rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @scallions{2%unit}, @plant-based pulled mushrooms{1%unit}, 
@white rice{3/4%cup}, @salt{}, @pepper{}, @cooking oil{}, and @sugar{}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water, and a 
pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. 
Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice radishes 
into rounds. Trim and thinly slice scallions, separating whites from greens. 
Halve pulled mushrooms lengthwise. Halve, peel, and thinly slice onion.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, 
@salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, 
~{15-20%minutes}.

== Pickled Carrots & Radish ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, half the 
@sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}, 1/2 tsp @sugar{}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. 
Stir in radishes, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, and scallion whites. Refrigerate 
until ready to serve.

== Mushrooms ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high 
heat. Add @plant-based pulled mushrooms{1%unit}; cook, stirring occasionally, 
until crisp and warmed through, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add onion and another drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}; cook, stirring 
occasionally, until onion is softened and translucent, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Reduce heat under pan to medium low and add @bulgogi sauce{4%ounce}. Stir until 
mushrooms and onion are evenly coated. Taste and season with @salt{} and 
@pepper{}. Turn off heat.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Divide rice, mushrooms and onion, broccoli, and pickled veggies between plates 
in separate sections. Drizzle with as much @spicy mayo{4%tablespoon} as you like. 
Garnish with remaining sesame seeds and scallion greens. Serve.